    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2005-05-16</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2005-06-27T18:53:33Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>In Memory Medal For Forgotten Veterans Act - Establishes the &quot;Jesus (Chuchi) Salgado Medal&quot; to be issued by the Secretary of Defense to a qualifying veteran who: (1) died after serving in the Vietnam War but whose death is determined to be a direct result of such service; (2) was exposed to herbicide agents while serving in the Republic of Vietnam and is eligible for health care; (3) was exposed to ionizing radiation and is eligible for health care; or (4) served in Southwest Asia during the Persian Gulf War and is entitled (or was at the time of death entitled) to disability benefits for illnesses associated with Gulf War service.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>In Memory Medal For Forgotten Veterans Act</title>
    <titles>
      <item>
